result.execSummary:
The defendant Leah R Paczkowski was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Leah R Paczkowski in court with attorney Maura O'Connell Melka.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the defendant has a money order for the clerk of courts for $913.94.  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Counts 1 & 2.  Atty Hendee asks the court to order the COC to pay out Restitution.
Atty Melka agrees.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 & 2.

Atty Hendee asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.    State has complied with victim notification requirements.  Court reads the victim impact statement.
Attty Melka makes a statement to the court and asks the court to follow the recommendation.

BY THE COURT:  Counts 1 & 2:  Withhold Sentence; 9 months Probation with conditions:
*Court Costs = $243.00 on each count
* DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
*Restitutiton = $830.86 + $83.08 surcharge = $913.94
*AODA and any follow-up treatment
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent

COC to pay out Restitution
Defendant is to report to the Probation office by the end of business next Tuesday, Dec. 22nd due to the office being closed today.

BY THE COURT:  Set for Plea/sentencing
bond continued.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 17, 2015 at 10:30 am.
